    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-10-12T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-10-12T19:00:00-05:00" n="290"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d290">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.24/259: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-10-12T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >October 12, 1942—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>267. Your 312, October 6, and Department’s 257, October 2 and 207, August 8.
                    Please advise Foreign Minister that Department believes Iranian Government has
                    taken wise step in approving appointment of Millspaugh. You may renew previous
                    assurances that we will cooperate closely in selection of assistants and may say
                    that Millspaugh has expressed his desire for such cooperation. He will proceed
                    immediately to discuss terms of contract with Iranian Minister here and you will
                    be fully informed in this regard.</p>
                <p>We note from your 312 that Millspaugh appointment was opposed by Minister of
                    Finance. Please take first opportunity to reiterate to Foreign Minister views
                    expressed in Department’s 207, August 8. <pb facs="0270" n="258" xml:id="pg_258"
                    /> We believe Iranian Government will agree this mission is most important of
                    all those now being organized and that its success is vital to the achievement
                    of Cabinet’s policy of reform and reconstruction with American assistance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
